{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17643262","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17643262"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T19:51:37+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T19:51:37+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17993"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17993","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17993"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10707"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78829"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10707","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10707"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17993"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64178"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"4947"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"24927"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24928"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27033"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78829","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/78829"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EExercise can have considerable health benefits.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following conditions can have symptom control with high-level exercise?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Asthma","Depression","Diabetes mellitus","Hypertension","Osteoarthritis"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDepression\u003C/strong\u003E is a condition where high-level exercise can significantly help in symptom control. Regular physical activity has been shown to improve mood, reduce anxiety, and enhance overall mental well-being. Exercise releases endorphins, which are chemicals in the brain that act as natural painkillers and mood elevators. A systematic review in the British Medical Journal showed that exercise is an effective treatment for depression, with walking or jogging, yoga and strength training more effective than other exercises, particularly when intense.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAsthma\u003C/strong\u003E can be exacerbated by exercise, especially if not well-controlled, although regular, moderate exercise can improve lung function and overall fitness in asthmatic patients.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHypertension\u003C/strong\u003E can be managed with regular exercise, but it is not specifically controlled by high-level exercise alone. Lifestyle modifications, including diet and medication, are also important.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDiabetes mellitus\u003C/strong\u003E benefits from regular exercise as it helps in controlling blood glucose levels, but high-level exercise is not specifically required for symptom control.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOsteoarthritis\u003C/strong\u003E can benefit from low-impact exercise to maintain joint function and reduce pain, but high-level exercise may exacerbate symptoms due to increased joint stress.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["High-level exercise can be beneficial in managing symptoms of depression.","Exercise has been shown to improve mood and reduce anxiety.","Regular physical activity can enhance overall mental well-being."],"references":["Moghetti P, Bacchi E, Brangani C, Don\u00e0 S, Negri C. Metabolic Effects of Exercise. Front Horm Res. 2016;47:44-57. doi: 10.1159/000445156. Epub 2016 Jun 27. PMID: 27348753","Thyfault JP, Bergouignan A. Exercise and metabolic health: beyond skeletal muscle. Diabetologia. 2020 Aug;63(8):1464-1474. doi: 10.1007/s00125-020-05177-6. Epub 2020 Jun 11. PMID: 32529412; PMCID: PMC7377236","Keller J, 